Senate Resolution 268
By: Senator James of the 28th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing March 18, 2025, as International Diaspora Day at the state capitol; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, many of the traditions we celebrate and practice in the United States originate
4 from the peoples of other continents; and
5 WHEREAS, the myriad of cultures that make up the United States are a reflection of the rich
6 history and traditions of the many nations and people who have immigrated to its shores; and
7 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia has been enriched by the presence of its citizens of
8 international heritage, who have made invaluable contributions to its political, social, and
9 economic prosperity; and
10 WHEREAS, the members of the Georgia General Assembly salute the presence,
11 productivity, and many contributions of those residents of international birth and lineage.
12 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
13 recognize March 18, 2025, as International Diaspora Day at the state capitol.
